RELEASE NOTES This is GENSYMCID-1884, regression test for GENSYMCID-1181 'Readout-table format'
BACKGROUND In some versions of G2, readout-tables didn't display float values properly.
SOLUTION We reused pre-existing test kb. Testrail case and test kb from GENSYMCID-1181 do not match the bug description. It is expected that freeform-table displayed values should change when float-to-text-default-format of miscellanous-parameters is changed. But this is not the case for test kb. We don't know if this is due to bug or this is normal combination of settings of test-class, its instances and freeform-table. Our knowledge of product is limited and our task was not to investigate specifically this question.
So we simply inserted "update" for freeform-table to make sure displays change. Our test scenario does not match that of testrail anymore: freeform-table displayed values change after float-to-text-default-format changes in our test. In testrail test it is specified that they should not change. We believe it makes the test more worthy because testrail case checks readout-table formats while we check both readout-table and freeform-table.
TESTING We compared current behavior for "default" setting to the ver8.4(default).png found in testrail and found that current version is correct when setting is "default". We used that to make expected results for "default" setting in our test case.
For other float-to-text-default-format settings, we use actual data generated for each float-to-text-default format as setting in current build of G2 (HIP2016-09). So we created a regression test but we didn't check if the bug presents in current G2 version.
